A MAN and a woman have been killed in a road smash between a motorcycle and a car.
The dead pair, believed to be in their 20s, were travelling on the orange KTM motorbike when it was involved in a collision with an Alfa Romeo in Aberdeen last night.
The tragedy happened on Hilton Drive around 8.50pm, Police Scotland confirmed.
The road was closed for several hours to allow officers to carry out an investigation into the exact circumstances.
A police spokesman said: “Police in Aberdeen were called to a serious road collision in Hilton Drive where sadly two people have died.
“Inquiries into the full circumstances surrounding this collision are ongoing.
“We are appealing for any witnesses to the incident to call 101 with their information.”
